	<center><h1>Getting your Parts</h1></center>

	<div class="content">	
		<h2>Software</h2>
		<p>The open-source <a href="https://www.arduino.cc/">Arduino IDE</a> software is available for Windows PC, Mac OS X, and linux, and it is free. </p>
		<div class="windows">
			<center><h4>For Windows</h4></center>
			<p>Download the Arduino IDE software for Windows here, and then run the installation program.</p>
			<p>You will also need to install either this driver or this driver. After downloading the driver, extract the folder from the zip file and then run the setup program inside the folder. </p>
		</div>
		<div class="mac">
			<center><h4>For Macs</h4></center>
			<p>Download the Arduino IDE software for Macs here. </p>
			<p>You will also need to install this driver.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="circuit">
			<center><h4>Circuit Drawing Program</h4></center>
			<p>Fritzing is a free open-source circuit drawing program that is very useful for teachers who want to draw their own Arduino circuits. All of the circuit pictures found in these tutorials are done with Fritzing. Furthermore, there is an option to professionally custom make a PCB board of your circuit</p>
		</div>

		<h2>Hardware</h2>
		<p>Email to <a href="mailto:parts@robotsforfun.com">parts@robotsforfun.com</a> if you want to purchase any of the following kits and parts.</p>
		<p>You can pay with cash, check, or your PayPal account using the "Send Money to Friends and Family" option and pay to <a href="mailto:payment@robotsforfun.com">payment@robotsforfun.com</a>.</p>

